Content: [Regnar#6164] The thing about that is, everything in life is technically open source and can be copied, but we still give much more weight to the things that are done by professionals because they can fix things when they break, know the ins and outs, and have the knowledge to apply the right tools where they belong

Author: Komodo-Bot#0171
Content: [Regnar#6164] obviously we have copyrights, but i'm talking about services

Author: Komodo-Bot#0171
Content: [Regnar#6164] anyone can copy techniques that consultants use. or copy techniques that carpenters, mechanics, artists, or anything, but having the blue prints isn't enough.

Author: Komodo-Bot#0171
Content: [Robert Naus#9564] 1st mover advantage is the key

Author: Komodo-Bot#0171
Content: [Regnar#6164] Blockchain as a Service is about the people who intimately know the chains, and process, and know the code, providing not just the code as a product, but their expertise as a service. that is valuable
